                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2017",
                     "month": "6",
                     "day": "13"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "On this image, we see an Indigenous man holding a quipu (knotted cords), with a numerical value indicated on the right. To the left, there is a Yupana—a board with dots representing numbers, possibly associated with finger counting.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p> In this system, the absence of a knot represents zero (0). Each knot added signifies an increase in value, with the maximum being nine (9). After reaching this limit, knots are added in the row above (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('6e9bef8c-6ec5-4c04-b583-aea8e6bbec5b'); return false;\">Quesada, Eugenio de, <htdate0></a>):</p><p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgAndesQuipu\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgAndesQuipu', '0%')\" src=\"images/Andes_Quipu.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 3</b>: Quipu representation. The source code is available in GitHub of the project (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers, <htdate1>, Source-code</a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2016",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2024",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><h4>The Yuapana</h4>The <i>\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay\"</i> method utilized on this page was developed and published by Dhavit Prem (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit</a>) of the Yupanki Association (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit, <htdate0>, pp. 354 - 363</a>). This method follows the vertical model of <i>Yupana</i>, as presented by Felipe Guaman Poma de Ayala (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('f5b74f18-0bc4-46d2-8a5c-64dd80b74dd1'); return false;\">Poma de Ayala, Felipe Guaman, <htdate1>, pp. 361 - 362</a>). When the maximum value, nine (9), is reached, calculations continue in the row above.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2018",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "1615",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\"><i>Yupana</i></th><th>Hindu-Arabic numbers</th><th>Arrows</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f1\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f1\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f1\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td><td id=\"tc5f1\" rowspan=\"2\"><span class=\"text_to_paint\" id=\"andesIndoArabic\">0</span></td><td id=\"tc6f1\" rowspan=\"2\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" name=\"yupanaUp\"></i>  <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\"style=\"font-size:4em;color:#00f;\" name=\"yupanaDown\"></td></tr>  <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\"><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_center\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c1_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_up\"></span><span class=\"dot five_dot_c2_bottom\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc2f2\"><span class=\"dot three_dot_bottom\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_up\"></span><span class=\"dot three_dot_center\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc3f2\"><span class=\"dot two_dot_bottom\"></span> <span class=\"dot two_dot_up\"></span></td> <td id=\"tc4f2\"><span class=\"dot dot_center\"></span></td></tr></table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_conclusion",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Conclusion</h3>Regardless of the numerical system, the principle of respecting the maximum and minimum limits remains consistent. This text illustrates how different indigenous cultures developed analogous ideas about growth, likely inspired by observations of nature and its processes.</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      }
